Thanks to the ZSH team, the necessary changes have been made and  
ZSH 3.0.2 now works fantastically with NeXTStep on my 68040/25MHz  
mono machine.

If there is sufficient interest I will put together a QuadFat  
distribution for NeXTStep.  Email me if you're interested.

Thanks to Wolfgang Hukriede <whukriede@ifm.uni-kiel.de> who  
discovered the fix, and Zoltan Hidvegi <hzoli@cs.elte.hu> who  
repacked 3.0.2 to include the necessary fix.

ZSH can be found here:

